<subSubSection id="C9958CB369588502F6DEF8DEFDD0F79E" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8130DF3869588502F6DEF8DEFE0DF8EB" blockId="2.[136,1452,1152,2079]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis id="B3FB032A69588502F6DEF8DEFE9FF8A3" bold="true" box="[189,294,1800,1826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">Ecology:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="468FA4BB69588502F721F8DEFDAEF8A3" authorityName="Liang Zhang &amp; Li Bing Zhang, OL" authorityYear="2022" box="[322,535,1800,1826]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Athyriaceae" genus="Athyrium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aberrans">
<emphasis id="B3FB032A69588502F721F8DEFDAEF8A3" box="[322,535,1800,1826]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">Athyrium aberrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was observed to be terrestrial in wetlands in the open areas in the forests of the Deergong Basin, at elevations between 1640 and 
<quantity id="467772DD69588502F4A0F8FAFCA7F8C6" box="[707,798,1836,1863]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" unit="m" value="1650.0">1650 m</quantity>
. High humidity and sufficient light are important for the growth of the new species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8130DF3869588502F6DEF8A2FDD0F79E" blockId="2.[136,1452,1152,2079]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis id="B3FB032A69588502F6DEF8A2FE52F80F" bold="true" box="[189,491,1908,1934]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">IUCN Red List category:</emphasis>
—Only two populations with about 40 individuals of 
<taxonomicName id="468FA4BB69588502F22BF8A2FAA4F80F" authorityName="Liang Zhang &amp; Li Bing Zhang, OL" authorityYear="2022" box="[1096,1309,1908,1934]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Athyriaceae" genus="Athyrium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aberrans">
<emphasis id="B3FB032A69588502F22BF8A2FAA4F80F" box="[1096,1309,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">Athyrium aberrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found. The status of the new species can be classified as Critically Endangered (CR), based on current information and following the International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources (IUCN) guidelines (IUCN, 2011), but more extensive fieldwork focusing on the similar habit of the 
<typeStatus id="5E34619A69588502F5C6F837FC6CF87A" box="[933,981,2017,2043]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">type</typeStatus>
locality in the nearby mountains is needed to accurately assess its conservation status.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C9958CB369598503F6DEFF48FB64FEA4" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8130DF3869598503F6DEFF48FB7CFE81" blockId="3.[136,1451,158,293]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis id="B3FB032A69598503F6DEFF48FEF1FF39" bold="true" box="[189,328,158,184]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">Etymology:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B3FB032A69598503F72BFF49FED8FF39" box="[328,353,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">—</emphasis>
The species epithet from the Latin, 
<emphasis id="B3FB032A69598503F490FF48FCE1FF39" box="[755,856,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">aberrans</emphasis>
, abnormal, referring to purplish stipe and rachis and scaled bulbil of the new species which is uncommon in the genus. Besides, the new species could be confused with some species of 
<taxonomicName id="468FA4BB69598503F723FF30FD31FE80" authority="Swartz (1801: 61)" authorityName="Swartz" authorityPageNumber="61" authorityYear="1801" box="[320,648,230,257]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Athyriaceae" genus="Diplazium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B3FB032A69598503F723FF30FE0CFE81" box="[320,437,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">Diplazium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E51EA2C969598503F7DFFF30FD31FE80" author="Swartz, O." box="[444,648,230,257]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="1 - 120" refId="ref3414" refString="Swartz, O. (1801) Genera et species filicum ordine systematico redactarum. Journal fur die Botanik. H. A. Schrader, Gottingen 1800 (2): 1 - 120." type="journal article" year="1801">Swartz (1801: 61)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="468FA4BB69598503F4F7FF31FB88FE81" authority="T. Moore (1857: 141)" authorityName="T. Moore" authorityPageNumber="141" authorityYear="1857" box="[660,1073,230,257]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Athyriaceae" genus="Diplazium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longifolium">
<emphasis id="B3FB032A69598503F4F7FF31FC8EFE81" box="[660,823,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">D. longifolium</emphasis>
T. 
<bibRefCitation id="E51EA2C969598503F538FF31FB88FE81" author="Moore, T." box="[859,1073,230,257]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" refId="ref3161" refString="Moore, T. (1857) Index Filicum, a synopsis with characters of the genera, and an enumeration of the species of ferns, with synonyms, references, etc. W. Pamplin, London, 168 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 55301" type="book" year="1857">Moore (1857: 141)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
for example.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8130DF3869598503F6DEFEDCFB64FEA4" blockId="3.[136,1451,158,293]" box="[189,1245,266,293]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis id="B3FB032A69598503F6DEFEDCFE32FEA5" bold="true" box="[189,395,266,292]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">Vernacular name</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="B3FB032A69598503F7F2FEDDFE14FEA5" box="[401,429,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">—</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B3FB032A69598503F7CDFEDDFD83FEA3" bold="true" box="[430,570,267,290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">ǿ异fiǎƀ</emphasis>
(qi yi ti gai jue, which means a special species of 
<taxonomicName id="468FA4BB69598503F206FEDCFB74FEA5" box="[1125,1229,266,292]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Athyriaceae" genus="Athyrium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B3FB032A69598503F206FEDCFB74FEA5" box="[1125,1229,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">Athyrium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
